. Caldwell presents the dacha world in all its richness and complexity-a "good life" that draws inspiration from the natural environment in which it is situated.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCountry homesxRussia (Federation). 0aCountry homeszRussia (Federation) 0aGardeningxRussia (Federation). 0aGardeningzRussia (Federation) 0aOrganic livingxRussia (Federation). 0aOrganic livingzRussia (Federation) 0aVacation homesxRussia (Federation). 0aVacation homeszRussia (Federation) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947870423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520947870.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles